-- SEC's Cox actively monitoring market developments
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2008 4:56pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/11/us-lehman-sec-idUSWBT00967720080911

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission Chairman Christopher Cox and top agency officials are actively monitoring market developments and have been regularly discussing them with market participants, an SEC spokesman said on Thursday. 

 SEC spokesman John Nester declined to comment on Lehman Brothers, whose shares were down 41 percent in Thursday morning trading. (Reporting by  Rachelle Younglai ; Editing by  Tim Dobbyn )